&lt;h1 id=&#34;000164&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#000164&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 000164&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear Jim,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wow, what an absolute thrill to hear from you! Knowing you’re about to dive headfirst into a UN poll, I simply &lt;em&gt;must&lt;/em&gt; share some groundbreaking insights that will surely revolutionize everything.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First off, I couldn’t think of a nobler cause than demanding that scientific institutions and governments throw obscene amounts of money into neko-musume conversion projects—because clearly, humanity’s most urgent priority. Forget climate change or world peace; what we really need is genetically engineered cat-girls to save the day! Expertise? Pfft. Just analyze the biological basis and ignore all those pesky environmental, social, political, and ethical dilemmas that might ruin your day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And why stop there? Neko-musumes are just adorable humanoids with cat ears that squeal “nyan” instead of “meow”—who wouldn’t want more of that? Plus, they’re &lt;em&gt;obvious&lt;/em&gt; game-changers for the workforce, as seen in countless anime maid cafés, providing some much-needed relief from the crushing labor shortages caused by our heartbreaking aging crisis. Forget robots or policies; just spin up a few neko-musumes and watch productivity skyrocket.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I truly hope my totally serious advice can inspire your proposal. Haven’t seen a real neko-musume yet? No worries! Just ring up my pal Clare L. Halifax—she’s got the inside scoop. And if you’ve ever dreamed of becoming one yourself, I’ve got those &lt;em&gt;magical pills&lt;/em&gt; that transform you overnight—because, obviously, that’s the pinnacle of scientific progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bye-bye for now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yours, Li Hua&lt;br /&gt;
