&lt;h1 id=&#34;000185&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#000185&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; 000185&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear Jim,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oh, what an incredible, jaw-dropping honor it is to &lt;em&gt;hear&lt;/em&gt; from you! And to think you’re about to plunge headlong into a UN poll—my goodness, I can hardly contain my outrage! I &lt;em&gt;must&lt;/em&gt; blast through this so-called &amp;quot;news&amp;quot; with the fury it deserves and unload these &lt;em&gt;groundbreaking&lt;/em&gt; insights—well, not that anyone asked for them—because frankly, this whole nonsense is the very reason I lose sleep at night.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First of all, how dare you even entertain the notion that the highest priority of scientific institutions and governments should be pouring obscene amounts of money into neko-musume conversion schemes?! Are you serious?! Humanity’s so-called &amp;quot;most urgent priorities&amp;quot; are apparently now pet projects for your bizarre fantasies. Climate change? Don’t make me laugh. World peace? Please. What we &lt;em&gt;really&lt;/em&gt; need is to crank out genetically engineered cat-girls—yes, &lt;em&gt;cat-girls&lt;/em&gt;!—to fix everything?! Are you utterly blind to the disaster you&#39;re suggesting? Expertise? Ha! Just skim the biological basis and ignore the chaos of environmental ruin, social upheavals, political disasters, and ethical nightmares. Because why not throw ethics out the window while you&#39;re at it?!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And don’t even think for half a second that’s where it stops. No, neko-musumes—those cutesy humanoid creatures with ears that screech “nyan”—are obviously the answer to every problem! Who wouldn’t want more of that delusional cuteness? Plus, they’re &lt;em&gt;obvious&lt;/em&gt; saviors for the workforce—who cares about real jobs, real people, or the crushing reality of aging populations—just spin up a few neko-musumes and watch the productivity miracles happen! Never mind the chaos that will inevitably ensue—what’s meant to be convenient and adorable is all that matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I sincerely hope my &lt;em&gt;dead serious&lt;/em&gt; advice sparks some of that brilliant, reckless inspiration you seem to crave. Haven’t seen a real neko-musume in action? Don’t worry—just call Clare L. Halifax; she’s got all the &lt;em&gt;inside&lt;/em&gt; scoop on this madness. And if you’re dreaming of transforming into one yourself, oh, I’ve got those &lt;em&gt;magical pills&lt;/em&gt; that can turn you into a neko-musume overnight—because, obviously, that’s &lt;em&gt;ultimate&lt;/em&gt; scientific progress. Heaven forbid we focus on real, meaningful solutions!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Goodbye now—you’re welcome for the unsolicited dose of truth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yours, Li Hua&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;ins&gt;2025-8-23 12:56:32&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
